"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-lifestyle-celeb-news-international-celebs-snoop-dogg-joins-team-usa-a-new-era-for-the-paris-olympics\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbLifestyle\\u00bbCeleb News\\u00bbInternational Celebs\\u00bbSnoop Dogg joins Team USA: A new era for the Paris Olympics  Snoop Dogg has officially joined Team USA for the Paris Olympics, taking on the role of commentator and correspondent.  Snoop Dogg has officially joined Team USA for the Paris Olympics.  The legendary rapper and actor, known for his larger-than-life persona, has taken on a new role as a commentator and correspondent.  The 52-year-old rapper, who has always been a fan favourite, has now officially entered the Olympic arena, according toThe Sports Rush.  The excitement around his inclusion is palpable, with Team USA's social media pages buzzing with anticipation.  Snoop's official Team USA headshot session was nothing short of a spectacle.  Dressed in a blue durag, Nike hoodie, and track pants, he added a touch of his unique style with a T-shirt featuring a dramatic graphic of sprinting star Noah Lyles.  As he settled in for the photo shoot, he made one thing clear: he wanted the world to see that T-shirt, according toSports Illustrated.  \\\"Make sure you get that GOAT,\\\" he told the photographer, referring to the bold graphic of Lyles.  Lyles has recently become a sensation in the track and field world.  The rapper's headshots mark his formal entry into the team as a prominent public figure.  Not just a commentator, Snoop will be part of the Olympic coverage team, bringing his distinctive flair to the global stage.  His outfit was as much a statement as his role. \\\"It's official like a referee with a whistle,\\\" Snoop declared.  This encapsulated his excitement and the gravity of the moment, according toSportskeeda.  The story does not end with the headshots. Snoop Dogg recently teamed up with Noah Lyles for an extraordinary event.  The two stars unveiled a collection of rare Yu-Gi-Oh cards, showcasing Lyles' passion for anime and collectible cards.  Fans of Lyles know him for his Yu-Gi-Oh card collection, which he often flaunts during races.  This collaboration was a special treat for fans of both stars.  In a playful and highly anticipated unboxing session, Snoop and Lyles revealed the contents of a mysterious briefcase.  The briefcase, packed with some of the rarest Yu-Gi-Oh cards, was a perfect blend of sports and pop culture.  Snoop's enthusiasm was palpable. \\\"I have always been a huge supporter of Noah,\\\" Snoop said.  \\\"This was just another way to show it.\\\"  Snoop Dogg's role in the Paris Olympics is set to be a game-changer.  His charisma and unique perspective will undoubtedly add a fresh dimension to the Olympiccoverage.  With his blend of sportsmanship and showmanship, he is poised to make a significant impact.  As Team USA gears up for Paris, Snoop Dogg's addition is already stirring excitement.  His flair, combined with his love for sports and entertainment, promises to bring a new level of energy to the Olympics.  Fans can look forward to seeing Snoop's dynamic presence on and off the screen.  The Paris Games are shaping up to be one of the most memorable yet, with Snoop Dogg making sure he leaves his special mark.  Let us know by clicking on the comment tab below this article or by emailinginfo@thesouthafrican.comor sending a WhatsApp to 060 011 021 1.  You can also follow@TheSAnews on XandThe South African on Facebookfor the latest news.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African 